ğŸ§  Analogy

Think of a Kubernetes cluster as a company building:â€‹

    Cluster-Scoped Resources: These are like the building's infrastructureâ€”elevators, security systems, or the main power supplyâ€”that serve the entire building.â€‹

    Namespaced Resources: These are like individual offices or departments within the building, each with its own equipment, staff, and access controls.â€‹

This structure allows multiple teams to operate independently within the same cluster, ensuring organization, security, and efficient resource utilization


